          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Optional: Soak the chickpeas in filtered water overnight and maybe add a strip of kombu seaweed too (helps with gas, supposedly). Drain and rinse before proceeding to the next step."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "f40e9d53-7fb2-47b5-b90b-783b44f54bcf",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add the chickpeas to the insert of an Instant Pot and cover with water by 3-4 inches."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "1846289c-2abc-4744-aef6-cc2c3cd288d4",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Set the Instant Pot to High Pressure, and adjust the timer to 35 minutes (12 minutes if using soaked chickpeas)"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "fe788f15-9103-46f4-9d9e-043fad809584",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "When the cooking time is up, turn off the Instant Pot and wait 15-20 minutes, then release any remaining pressure before unlocking the lid."
        },
        {
